WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.708 --> 00:00:08.500
[wind whistling]

2
00:00:08.583 --> 00:00:10.625
[helicopter propellers beating]

3
00:00:12.417 --> 00:00:14.708
[dramatic music playing]

4
00:00:15.875 --> 00:00:17.292
[cell phone vibrating]

5
00:00:18.458 --> 00:00:19.333
[Philip] Answer it.

6
00:00:21.125 --> 00:00:22.583
-Hello?
-[man on phone]Mr. Burroughs.

7
00:00:22.667 --> 00:00:24.417
My name is Detective Wayne Semsey.

8
00:00:24.500 --> 00:00:26.042
Is Warden Mackenzie okay?

9
00:00:26.125 --> 00:00:28.417
Tell them to back off.
pull the spike strip.

10
00:00:28.500 --> 00:00:29.917
or I'm gonna shoot him in the head.

11
00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:33.542
Confirmed. Suspect is armed
with a handgun on the hostage.

12
00:00:33.625 --> 00:00:36.167
[Semsey]Listen to me. David.
We can figure this out. all right--?

13
00:00:36.250 --> 00:00:38.333
Shut up! You're not listening! Drive!

14
00:00:38.417 --> 00:00:40.292
[tires screech]

15
00:00:42.375 --> 00:00:44.833
Suspect approaching
200 yards out. please advise.

16
00:00:44.917 --> 00:00:46.292
Listen to me. David. David--

17
00:00:46.375 --> 00:00:49.042
Pull the strip.
or I'll put a bullet in his head!

18
00:00:49.125 --> 00:00:50.625
Please. David. don't do this!

19
00:00:50.708 --> 00:00:53.083
-[David]Pull the strip!
-A hundred yards.

20
00:00:53.667 --> 00:00:55.250
[David]Pull the goddamn strip!

21
00:00:55.333 --> 00:00:57.250
Goddamn it. I'm gonna kill him!

22
00:00:57.333 --> 00:00:58.500
Pull the strip!

23
00:00:58.583 --> 00:01:00.375
-Fifty.
-[Philip] Pull the strip!

24
00:01:01.208 --> 00:01:02.750
[suspenseful music playing]

25
00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:10.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

26
00:01:15.375 --> 00:01:16.458
Now what?

27
00:01:17.083 --> 00:01:18.458
I'm open to suggestions.

28
00:01:21.375 --> 00:01:23.917
Burroughs's case
made national news five years ago

29
00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:27.667
when he was tried and convicted
for the murder of his three-year-old son.

30
00:01:27.750 --> 00:01:29.125
Matthew Burroughs.

31
00:01:29.208 --> 00:01:31.917
The nation had trouble reconciling
how a man could bludgeon

32
00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:35.958
his own son to death
with a baseball bat as he slept.

33
00:01:36.042 --> 00:01:38.375
So where is David Burroughs now?

34
00:01:39.292 --> 00:01:40.500
Hello?

35
00:01:40.583 --> 00:01:42.292
[David. on phone]Rachel. it's David.

36
00:01:46.417 --> 00:01:48.875
David. What the hell is going on?

37
00:01:48.958 --> 00:01:51.333
I didn't mean to drag you into this.
but I need your help.

38
00:01:51.417 --> 00:01:53.000
[distant police sirens]

39
00:01:54.458 --> 00:01:55.458
[Ted] Hey!

40
00:01:55.542 --> 00:01:56.625
[alarm buzzing]

41
00:01:56.708 --> 00:01:57.958
Hello. Theodore.

42
00:01:58.875 --> 00:02:00.500
I hear Burroughs flew the coop.

43
00:02:00.583 --> 00:02:03.417
Listen to me. you piece of shit.
You tell them I'm out.

44
00:02:03.500 --> 00:02:04.500
Out?

45
00:02:05.125 --> 00:02:08.792
You were supposed to kill him.
and now he's a free man.

46
00:02:08.875 --> 00:02:12.167
-This wasn't my fault!
-Of course it was.

47
00:02:12.250 --> 00:02:13.750
But that's not your real problem.

48
00:02:13.833 --> 00:02:18.375
Your real problem is
you've been taking their money for years.

49
00:02:18.458 --> 00:02:20.708
I will pay them back. All of it.

50
00:02:20.792 --> 00:02:22.167
Even if you could.

51
00:02:23.417 --> 00:02:26.042
money leaves a trail.

52
00:02:26.125 --> 00:02:30.542
You. Teddy. you're a loose end.

53
00:02:31.333 --> 00:02:35.042
My advice? Take a page from Burroughs.

54
00:02:36.417 --> 00:02:39.375
Run. Teddy. Run.

55
00:02:41.750 --> 00:02:42.917
[phone ringing]

56
00:02:43.000 --> 00:02:44.583
[Semsey]David. glad you called back.

57
00:02:44.667 --> 00:02:46.708
No. no. shut up. all right?
Tell the cops to back off.

58
00:02:46.792 --> 00:02:49.458
-And lose the chopper.
-I will. Just remain calm. David.

59
00:02:49.542 --> 00:02:52.500
[officer on radio]They're turning
into the Greenville Outlet Mall.

60
00:02:52.583 --> 00:02:54.208
[helicopter propellers beating]

61
00:02:54.292 --> 00:02:56.958
They entered the parking garage.
We've lost visual.

62
00:02:57.042 --> 00:03:00.417
David. we don't want to involve
innocent people here. right?

63
00:03:00.500 --> 00:03:01.833
[officer 1]We have visual again.

64
00:03:01.917 --> 00:03:03.375
They've left the garage
and are back on the road.

65
00:03:03.458 --> 00:03:05.250
[David]I told you to pull the chopper!

66
00:03:05.333 --> 00:03:06.458
Let the warden go. David.

67
00:03:07.542 --> 00:03:09.542
[David]Not until you pull the chopper!

68
00:03:10.125 --> 00:03:12.417
[Semsey]You let the warden go.
and I'll pull the chopper.

69
00:03:12.500 --> 00:03:15.708
[officer 1]They're slowing down.
Repeat. they're slowing down.

70
00:03:16.417 --> 00:03:19.208
The truck has stopped.
but the hostage is still inside.

71
00:03:19.292 --> 00:03:21.500
-Officers in position.
-[officer 2] Go! Go!

72
00:03:21.583 --> 00:03:24.042
Out of the truck! Out of the truck!

73
00:03:25.458 --> 00:03:26.708
Show me your hands!

74
00:03:26.792 --> 00:03:28.583
[suspenseful music playing]

75
00:03:29.250 --> 00:03:30.250
Go. go!

76
00:03:35.625 --> 00:03:37.833
-[officer 3]Suspect is not in the truck.
-David!

77
00:03:38.458 --> 00:03:40.125
What the hell is going on. David?

78
00:03:40.625 --> 00:03:42.167
Come on. David. Talk--

79
00:03:42.875 --> 00:03:44.417
[tires squealing]

80
00:03:49.625 --> 00:03:50.958
[tires screech]

81
00:03:52.625 --> 00:03:54.333
[distant police sirens]

82
00:04:01.083 --> 00:04:02.875
Holy shit.

83
00:04:04.208 --> 00:04:05.542
It's fine. Just drive.

84
00:04:05.625 --> 00:04:07.542
-I am driving. This is driving.
-Okay.

85
00:04:08.125 --> 00:04:09.792
Just. when did you decide
to break out of prison?

86
00:04:11.375 --> 00:04:12.458
Kinda just happened.

87
00:04:12.542 --> 00:04:15.292
Kinda just happened?
That doesn't really… Okay.

88
00:04:16.917 --> 00:04:17.958
You have a plan. right?

89
00:04:18.875 --> 00:04:21.333
-David.
-I do. but you're not gonna like it.

90
00:04:21.417 --> 00:04:22.500
Oh. Jesus.

91
00:04:23.167 --> 00:04:25.958
I'm aiding and abetting a fugitive.
I mean. how much worse can it get?

92
00:04:26.750 --> 00:04:28.125
Rachel. you need to turn around.

93
00:04:28.208 --> 00:04:30.000
Back to where the cops are?

94
00:04:30.083 --> 00:04:32.042
Rachel. you got to trust me. Turn around.

95
00:04:32.125 --> 00:04:34.458
[dramatic music playing]

96
00:04:47.167 --> 00:04:49.167
[ominous music playing]

97
00:04:54.167 --> 00:04:56.750
["Jumpin' Jack Flash"
by the Rolling Stones playing]

98
00:05:07.583 --> 00:05:09.542
♪ I was born♪

99
00:05:09.625 --> 00:05:12.208
♪In a crossfire hurricane… ♪

100
00:05:12.292 --> 00:05:15.625
Special Agent Williams.
Nice job on the Galvin case.

101
00:05:16.250 --> 00:05:17.458
Thanks.

102
00:05:17.542 --> 00:05:18.958
I'm Simmons. by the way.

103
00:05:22.708 --> 00:05:23.625
I know.

104
00:05:24.208 --> 00:05:26.667
We actually studied
a few of your cases at Quantico.

105
00:05:26.750 --> 00:05:28.958
It's a real honor to be working for you.

106
00:05:29.458 --> 00:05:30.500
Anything else?

107
00:05:31.083 --> 00:05:32.208
Chopra's looking for you.

108
00:05:32.792 --> 00:05:34.000
Maybe lead with that next time.

109
00:05:34.083 --> 00:05:36.583
♪ It's a gas. gas. gas ♪

110
00:05:37.125 --> 00:05:38.250
Damn it.

111
00:05:39.167 --> 00:05:40.625
[typing]

112
00:05:42.042 --> 00:05:43.833
-[knock on door]
-Got a second?

113
00:05:43.917 --> 00:05:45.125
Before you say anything.

114
00:05:45.208 --> 00:05:47.417
I followed protocol
commandeering that Mercedes

115
00:05:47.500 --> 00:05:49.917
no matter what that TikTok video
makes it look like.

116
00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:51.083
That's not why I'm here.

117
00:05:52.375 --> 00:05:55.208
Okay. um. then you can
forget what I just said.

118
00:05:57.542 --> 00:06:00.625
There's an opening
to lead the FTF out of Seattle.

119
00:06:00.708 --> 00:06:03.708
I know the agent in charge.
I'd like to recommend you for the job.

120
00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:05.833
Okay.

121
00:06:05.917 --> 00:06:08.000
I expected a little more enthusiasm.

122
00:06:08.083 --> 00:06:10.917
I-I am enthused. obviously. It's just…

123
00:06:11.958 --> 00:06:13.167
You caught me off guard.

124
00:06:13.250 --> 00:06:15.833
I always imagined
taking over here one day.

125
00:06:15.917 --> 00:06:18.583
You really think the great Max Williams
is ever gonna retire?

126
00:06:18.667 --> 00:06:20.708
-No.
-[both laugh]

127
00:06:21.417 --> 00:06:24.208
Listen. you are a good agent.

128
00:06:24.917 --> 00:06:26.583
But that's not enough.

129
00:06:26.667 --> 00:06:28.667
You need someone in your corner.

130
00:06:28.750 --> 00:06:32.542
But if I'm gonna go out on a limb.
I need to know you're ready.

131
00:06:32.625 --> 00:06:34.375
That you want this.

132
00:06:34.458 --> 00:06:35.500
I'm ready.

133
00:06:36.583 --> 00:06:37.875
I want this.

134
00:06:37.958 --> 00:06:39.167
Good.

135
00:06:39.250 --> 00:06:40.667
[knock on door]

136
00:06:40.750 --> 00:06:41.750
Grab your stuff.

137
00:06:41.833 --> 00:06:44.750
-What's going on?
-David Burroughs just escaped from Briggs.

138
00:06:44.833 --> 00:06:46.375
[tense music playing]

139
00:06:50.708 --> 00:06:52.333
[Williams] All right. everybody on me!

140
00:06:52.417 --> 00:06:54.042
Details are still coming in.

141
00:06:54.125 --> 00:06:57.875
but we do know that Burroughs kidnapped
the warden before disappearing on his own.

142
00:06:58.458 --> 00:07:00.042
He's armed. Very dangerous.

143
00:07:00.125 --> 00:07:02.042
Been on the run for about an hour.

144
00:07:02.125 --> 00:07:03.375
What was this guy in for?

145
00:07:03.458 --> 00:07:05.583
-You're not from Boston. are you?
-No. why?

146
00:07:05.667 --> 00:07:09.000
Guy beat his own child to death
with a baseball bat five years ago.

147
00:07:10.333 --> 00:07:11.958
Prep packets are on board.

148
00:07:12.542 --> 00:07:14.167
Flight time is one hour.

149
00:07:14.250 --> 00:07:18.708
I want everyone up to speed
by the time we touch down.

150
00:07:18.792 --> 00:07:20.667
[helicopter propellers beating]

151
00:07:21.500 --> 00:07:22.542
Not you.

152
00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:26.542
What were you and Julie talking about?

153
00:07:27.750 --> 00:07:29.542
That stupid TikTok video.

154
00:07:29.625 --> 00:07:31.583
[cell phone vibrating]

155
00:07:33.708 --> 00:07:34.958
Agent Williams.

156
00:07:36.792 --> 00:07:39.208
What? No. No.

157
00:07:39.292 --> 00:07:41.958
Keep them separated.
We'll be there in an hour.

158
00:07:43.792 --> 00:07:47.833
Apparently. the warden's son
was found tied up in his office.

159
00:07:47.917 --> 00:07:49.667
-What?
-Yeah. it gets better.

160
00:07:49.750 --> 00:07:51.333
That's where Burroughs got the uniform.

161
00:07:51.417 --> 00:07:53.167
The warden's son is a cop?

162
00:07:53.250 --> 00:07:54.292
From Revere.

163
00:07:54.375 --> 00:07:58.583
I want to know everything there is to know
about these Mackenzies before we land.

164
00:07:58.667 --> 00:08:00.542
[dramatic music playing]

165
00:08:02.500 --> 00:08:04.500
[reporter] I'm on scene
at Briggs Penitentiary

166
00:08:04.583 --> 00:08:05.958
where just this morning.

167
00:08:06.042 --> 00:08:08.542
inmate David Burroughs
took the warden hostage

168
00:08:08.625 --> 00:08:11.083
and escaped through these very gates.

169
00:08:11.167 --> 00:08:15.208
Now. I can tell you that the warden
has since been released. however…

170
00:08:15.292 --> 00:08:16.583
I need to call Philip.

171
00:08:17.167 --> 00:08:21.167
Rachel. what the hell is going on?
You need to call me back. Please.

172
00:08:22.208 --> 00:08:23.167
[door opens]

173
00:08:23.250 --> 00:08:27.333
Hey. sweetheart. I just heard.
They're saying he took the warden hostage.

174
00:08:27.417 --> 00:08:28.833
-[door closes]
-Are you okay?

175
00:08:28.917 --> 00:08:30.708
No. Rachel was there.

176
00:08:31.875 --> 00:08:33.417
-Where?
-Briggs.

177
00:08:34.000 --> 00:08:36.208
She called me yesterday.
said she was visiting him.

178
00:08:37.875 --> 00:08:39.542
[indistinct chatter]

179
00:08:42.083 --> 00:08:43.083
[car door opens]

180
00:08:50.375 --> 00:08:52.000
This Wesson guy tried to kill you.

181
00:08:52.083 --> 00:08:53.833
You sure going to his house
is a good idea?

182
00:08:54.417 --> 00:08:56.000
He knows who has Matthew.

183
00:08:58.208 --> 00:08:59.750
You talk to your editor?

184
00:08:59.833 --> 00:09:02.000
Yeah. he's working on
getting us an address.

185
00:09:02.083 --> 00:09:03.500
You trust him?

186
00:09:03.583 --> 00:09:04.917
Jim? Yeah.

187
00:09:05.917 --> 00:09:07.583
Before you turned us
into Bonnie and Clyde.

188
00:09:07.667 --> 00:09:09.833
he was looking into Hilde Winslow for me.

189
00:09:09.917 --> 00:09:12.000
Turns out. after your trial.

190
00:09:12.083 --> 00:09:14.917
she changed her name. sold her house.

191
00:09:15.000 --> 00:09:16.583
and basically disappeared.

192
00:09:16.667 --> 00:09:18.833
-Disappeared?
-Yeah.

193
00:09:18.917 --> 00:09:22.458
He was able to dig up a PO box
in New York under her new name.

194
00:09:23.083 --> 00:09:23.917
Okay.

195
00:09:24.625 --> 00:09:26.208
[David breathing heavily]

196
00:09:29.083 --> 00:09:30.458
Hey. let me…

197
00:09:33.708 --> 00:09:35.833
It's okay. All these years.

198
00:09:38.125 --> 00:09:39.792
I should've done something.

199
00:09:43.750 --> 00:09:44.917
I'm sorry.

200
00:09:46.958 --> 00:09:49.417
Hey. you're here now.

201
00:09:53.042 --> 00:09:55.167
You know Bonnie and Clyde died. right?

202
00:09:55.833 --> 00:09:56.750
[cell phone pings]

203
00:10:00.583 --> 00:10:02.500
Jim's got Wesson's address.

204
00:10:03.625 --> 00:10:05.708
He lives less than ten miles from here.

205
00:10:09.167 --> 00:10:10.167
[cell phone ringing]

206
00:10:17.667 --> 00:10:18.542
Hello.

207
00:10:22.167 --> 00:10:23.792
And I can explain.

208
00:10:24.625 --> 00:10:28.042
You leave my family out of this!
They have nothing to do with it!

209
00:10:30.292 --> 00:10:31.792
I'll do whatever you say.

210
00:10:33.625 --> 00:10:34.625
Okay.

211
00:10:37.458 --> 00:10:39.000
You have my word.

212
00:10:39.083 --> 00:10:40.375
[phone beeps off]

213
00:10:44.417 --> 00:10:47.167
Hey. change of plans. uh. change of plans.

214
00:10:47.250 --> 00:10:50.458
You guys are gonna go up ahead.
and I will catch up later.

215
00:10:50.542 --> 00:10:52.375
You said that we were gonna go together.

216
00:10:53.250 --> 00:10:54.333
What's going on. Teddy?

217
00:10:54.917 --> 00:10:56.000
Nothing. It's…

218
00:10:56.083 --> 00:10:57.458
[scoffs]

219
00:10:57.542 --> 00:10:58.917
You gotta trust me on this.

220
00:10:59.000 --> 00:11:01.875
Um. you take Lisa.
you go to your sister's.

221
00:11:04.917 --> 00:11:06.875
-I love you.
-I love you.

222
00:11:07.542 --> 00:11:09.792
You be good for your mom. hmm?

223
00:11:10.375 --> 00:11:11.750
Why are you crying?

224
00:11:12.333 --> 00:11:13.500
Because I'm gonna…

225
00:11:14.083 --> 00:11:15.417
Because I'm gonna miss you.

226
00:11:15.500 --> 00:11:19.250
But you'll be there before bedtime. right?
We have to finishHarry Potter.

227
00:11:19.333 --> 00:11:20.500
[chuckles softly]

228
00:11:20.583 --> 00:11:22.708
I would like nothing more.

229
00:11:23.792 --> 00:11:25.417
I love you. Bug.

230
00:11:28.333 --> 00:11:30.542
[reporter]Briggs Penitentiary.
where just this morning…

231
00:11:30.625 --> 00:11:32.417
[sirens blaring]

232
00:11:33.917 --> 00:11:37.042
[Semsey] We have everyone in the state
looking for him. We'll find him.

233
00:11:37.125 --> 00:11:39.167
They've done a really good job so far.

234
00:11:39.250 --> 00:11:42.000
[Greer] Yeah. we're already here.
Might as well poke around a little.

235
00:11:42.083 --> 00:11:43.875
This is Deputy Warden Ralph Hitchens.

236
00:11:43.958 --> 00:11:46.417
He can answer
any of your operational questions.

237
00:11:46.500 --> 00:11:48.125
I'm gonna need
all visitor logs for Burroughs.

238
00:11:48.208 --> 00:11:51.208
plus a list of family. friends.
former inmates he might have crossed with.

239
00:11:51.292 --> 00:11:52.458
He's gonna need help on the outside.

240
00:11:52.542 --> 00:11:54.583
-I'm on it.
-So you say there's video?

241
00:11:54.667 --> 00:11:56.333
Yeah. Right here.

242
00:11:58.208 --> 00:12:01.208
[officer on radio]They entered
the parking garage. We've lost visual.

243
00:12:02.542 --> 00:12:05.708
We have visual again. They've left
the garage and are back on the road.

244
00:12:06.708 --> 00:12:07.917
Where are the warden
and his son right now?

245
00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:09.958
[Semsey] Being checked out
in the infirmary.

246
00:12:10.042 --> 00:12:13.875
Did the warden explain to you why he kept
driving if he was no longer a hostage?

247
00:12:13.958 --> 00:12:16.750
He said if he didn't. Burroughs would
start killing people at the mall.

248
00:12:16.833 --> 00:12:19.417
We searched the garage.
but we're not sure how he got out.

249
00:12:19.500 --> 00:12:24.125
Any reports of stolen cars from
the garage or carjackings in the area?

250
00:12:24.208 --> 00:12:25.125
No.

251
00:12:25.208 --> 00:12:26.167
Do the math.

252
00:12:27.292 --> 00:12:28.542
Someone picked him up.

253
00:12:29.167 --> 00:12:31.500
So you guys think he had an accomplice?

254
00:12:32.167 --> 00:12:34.250
Oh. he had more than one.

255
00:12:35.458 --> 00:12:37.125
Bring in the warden and his son.

256
00:12:38.083 --> 00:12:39.250
[Semsey] Right.

257
00:12:42.583 --> 00:12:44.208
[Williams] Any of this adding up for you?

258
00:12:44.292 --> 00:12:47.167
[scoffs] Not even a little.
Burroughs is a model prisoner.

259
00:12:47.250 --> 00:12:49.542
He hasn't had a single
incident report in five years.

260
00:12:49.625 --> 00:12:52.500
and then all of a sudden.
in the last three days.

261
00:12:52.583 --> 00:12:55.792
he nearly beats an inmate to death.
tries to kill a guard. and escapes?

262
00:12:58.792 --> 00:13:00.625
[Williams] So what happened
three days ago?

263
00:13:02.875 --> 00:13:04.000
[knock on door]

264
00:13:05.500 --> 00:13:06.917
-Warden Mackenzie.
-Yeah.

265
00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:08.333
Agent Williams. Agent Greer.

266
00:13:08.417 --> 00:13:09.792
Oh. yeah? Nice to meet you.

267
00:13:09.875 --> 00:13:12.542
-This is my son. Adam.
-Sounds like you had a hell of a morning.

268
00:13:12.625 --> 00:13:14.208
-[exhales]
-You can say that again.

269
00:13:14.292 --> 00:13:16.042
Well. we just gotta go over a few things.

270
00:13:16.125 --> 00:13:17.333
Of course. Happy to help.

271
00:13:17.417 --> 00:13:21.500
Hmm. Detective Semsey was kind enough
to give us your version of the events.

272
00:13:21.583 --> 00:13:22.417
Our version?

273
00:13:22.500 --> 00:13:24.875
How exactly
did David Burroughs get your gun?

274
00:13:25.458 --> 00:13:27.500
Uh. the inmate caught me off guard.

275
00:13:27.583 --> 00:13:29.750
Inmate? That's how you refer to him?

276
00:13:31.292 --> 00:13:32.792
-Excuse me?
-[Williams] Never mind that.

277
00:13:32.875 --> 00:13:37.958
We'll come back to it.
So. after the inmate caught you off guard.

278
00:13:38.042 --> 00:13:41.750
you just stripped down
and handed your uniform over.

279
00:13:43.625 --> 00:13:46.417
Uh. he had my gun.
What was I supposed to do?

280
00:13:46.500 --> 00:13:49.167
And was Burroughs handcuffed
during all of this. Officer Mackenzie?

281
00:13:49.750 --> 00:13:50.625
Yes.

282
00:13:51.333 --> 00:13:53.917
-And it's Sergeant Mackenzie.
-Oh. Sergeant.

283
00:13:55.125 --> 00:13:57.125
-You hear that. Sarah?
-I sure did.

284
00:13:57.708 --> 00:14:00.250
I guess they'll promote anybody
over at BPD.

285
00:14:00.333 --> 00:14:01.375
I guess so.

286
00:14:01.458 --> 00:14:05.250
Even a guy who's so inept.
he allowed a handcuffed inmate

287
00:14:05.333 --> 00:14:06.708
to reach into his jacket.

288
00:14:06.792 --> 00:14:09.375
unsnap his holster.
and pull out his pistol.

289
00:14:09.458 --> 00:14:13.042
You sure that's the statement
you want to stick with. Sergeant?

290
00:14:13.125 --> 00:14:14.750
Are you questioning my integrity?

291
00:14:14.833 --> 00:14:16.167
-What?
-You heard what I said.

292
00:14:16.250 --> 00:14:18.667
Take it easy. tiger.
How about you. Warden?

293
00:14:19.708 --> 00:14:22.542
Who do you think picked up Burroughs
after you dropped him off at the mall?

294
00:14:22.625 --> 00:14:24.167
Dropped him off?

295
00:14:24.250 --> 00:14:25.667
The inmate had a gun to my head.

296
00:14:25.750 --> 00:14:27.792
Told me to let him out. so I did.
End of story.

297
00:14:27.875 --> 00:14:29.625
Yeah. there goes that word again.

298
00:14:30.458 --> 00:14:31.458
"Inmate."

299
00:14:31.542 --> 00:14:34.417
You and David's father. Lenny.
worked Robbery-Homicide for 20 years.

300
00:14:34.500 --> 00:14:36.542
Adam and David grew up together.
You were family.

301
00:14:36.625 --> 00:14:38.583
Doesn't mean we helped.
In fact. that's probably--

302
00:14:38.667 --> 00:14:39.750
You know what? You're right.

303
00:14:39.833 --> 00:14:43.417
That's probably how Burroughs got the jump
on childhood best friend here.

304
00:14:43.500 --> 00:14:45.750
while you agreed to chauffeur.

305
00:14:45.833 --> 00:14:48.917
Quit talking to me like
I'm a goddamn idiot. Who picked him up?

306
00:14:50.458 --> 00:14:52.375
I think we're done talking
without a lawyer.

307
00:14:53.750 --> 00:14:54.917
[Hitchens] Agent Greer.

308
00:14:56.083 --> 00:14:57.333
Thank you.

309
00:14:57.417 --> 00:14:59.000
[Williams] What do you got there.
Agent Greer?

310
00:14:59.083 --> 00:15:01.167
-Visitor logs for David Burroughs.
-Oh.

311
00:15:02.125 --> 00:15:04.000
Anything interesting in there?

312
00:15:04.083 --> 00:15:05.208
I'd say so.

313
00:15:05.792 --> 00:15:08.292
Burroughs hasn't had a single visitor
for five years.

314
00:15:08.375 --> 00:15:11.833
but guess who showed up
three days ago before he escaped?

315
00:15:12.417 --> 00:15:13.250
Who?

316
00:15:13.333 --> 00:15:16.625
Rachel Mills. His ex-sister-in-law.

317
00:15:17.417 --> 00:15:19.208
[Williams] You don't say.

318
00:15:21.292 --> 00:15:23.750
Think we can get a BOLO out
on Rachel Mills?

319
00:15:23.833 --> 00:15:25.125
Mm-hmm.

320
00:15:28.417 --> 00:15:30.542
Looks like you and Sonny Boy
are gonna need that lawyer.

321
00:15:32.958 --> 00:15:34.167
[sighs]

322
00:15:40.083 --> 00:15:42.333
-We'll be at Wesson's in a few minutes.
-[cell phone vibrating]

323
00:15:46.125 --> 00:15:48.542
She's probably seen this
on the news by now.

324
00:15:49.333 --> 00:15:50.833
You know what?
I'm gonna power down anyway.

325
00:15:50.917 --> 00:15:52.417
The police can ping cell towers.

326
00:15:52.500 --> 00:15:54.292
Did you tell her about Matthew?

327
00:15:54.917 --> 00:15:56.208
I tried.

328
00:15:56.292 --> 00:15:57.417
Didn't go well.

329
00:15:58.750 --> 00:16:00.583
-Rachel…
-I know.

330
00:16:00.667 --> 00:16:02.125
It's not that simple.

331
00:16:03.667 --> 00:16:05.292
After Matthew…

332
00:16:07.708 --> 00:16:08.917
[sighs]

333
00:16:10.083 --> 00:16:14.000
I wasn't sure she'd be able
to put the pieces back together again.

334
00:16:14.083 --> 00:16:15.417
She finally has.

335
00:16:17.917 --> 00:16:19.458
So she's happy?

336
00:16:19.542 --> 00:16:20.667
Yeah.

337
00:16:21.500 --> 00:16:22.583
She's remarried.

338
00:16:25.083 --> 00:16:27.750
They're expecting a baby girl soon.

339
00:16:30.000 --> 00:16:31.875
I'm in charge of the baby shower.

340
00:16:31.958 --> 00:16:34.042
I mean. I'm not in charge. in charge.

341
00:16:34.125 --> 00:16:36.625
I'm more like a puppet dictator
quashing the dissidents

342
00:16:36.708 --> 00:16:38.667
who question the canapé selection.

343
00:16:38.750 --> 00:16:41.792
There's this one lady who keeps
wanting to cap the gift registry.

344
00:16:43.750 --> 00:16:44.833
I'm gonna shut up now.

345
00:16:49.542 --> 00:16:51.167
She always wanted a girl.

346
00:16:56.625 --> 00:16:59.125
[Williams] Show us the footage
from Rachel Mills's visit.

347
00:16:59.208 --> 00:17:02.750
Two visits. two video files.
Here's the first one.

348
00:17:04.583 --> 00:17:07.125
Huh. that's weird.
The video player won't open the file.

349
00:17:07.208 --> 00:17:08.417
I can see that. Why?

350
00:17:09.000 --> 00:17:11.583
No idea. It's never happened before.
Let me try the other one.

351
00:17:11.667 --> 00:17:12.708
[striking computer key]

352
00:17:14.042 --> 00:17:14.875
What the--

353
00:17:16.083 --> 00:17:17.833
-Hey. you can't just grab--
-All right.

354
00:17:17.917 --> 00:17:22.125
If the file is corrupt.
we might be able to repair it with a VLC.

355
00:17:22.208 --> 00:17:25.417
We just need to rename it as an AVI file.

356
00:17:25.500 --> 00:17:28.792
set preferences. and reopen.

357
00:17:29.792 --> 00:17:30.958
[computer beeping]

358
00:17:31.542 --> 00:17:33.750
Shit. The files aren't corrupt.

359
00:17:33.833 --> 00:17:36.625
They were erased
a few hours before we got here.

360
00:17:38.125 --> 00:17:41.542
Don't look at me. I took one online class
to learn the system. One.

361
00:17:41.625 --> 00:17:44.125
-Who's had access to the files?
-Any officer can access them.

362
00:17:44.208 --> 00:17:45.417
That narrows it down.

363
00:17:46.208 --> 00:17:47.708
Who escorted Burroughs down here?

364
00:17:48.875 --> 00:17:50.125
Officer Wesson.

365
00:17:50.833 --> 00:17:53.417
The same Ted Wesson
that Burroughs attacked last night?

366
00:17:53.500 --> 00:17:54.417
Yeah.

367
00:17:54.917 --> 00:17:57.333
-Where's Officer Wesson now?
-He went home this morning.

368
00:17:57.417 --> 00:18:00.333
Go to Officer Wesson's house
and drag his ass back here.

369
00:18:08.917 --> 00:18:10.333
[turns ignition off]

370
00:18:12.875 --> 00:18:14.375
There's no car out front.

371
00:18:16.542 --> 00:18:17.750
Maybe he's not home.

372
00:18:19.167 --> 00:18:21.125
Do you know if he has a family?

373
00:18:21.208 --> 00:18:23.083
He's married. He has a daughter.

374
00:18:24.667 --> 00:18:25.917
He told you he has a kid?

375
00:18:26.000 --> 00:18:29.833
I mean. in the context of it. he never
beat her to death with a baseball bat.

376
00:18:30.583 --> 00:18:31.542
Jesus.

377
00:18:32.458 --> 00:18:33.958
David. if his daughter's inside--

378
00:18:34.042 --> 00:18:36.500
He worked for the people who took Matthew.
He made his bed.

379
00:18:38.208 --> 00:18:39.542
[Rachel] Hey.

380
00:18:40.750 --> 00:18:42.292
I didn't sign up for that.

381
00:18:45.000 --> 00:18:46.667
Do we understand each other?

382
00:18:48.833 --> 00:18:50.292
[dramatic music playing]

383
00:19:12.292 --> 00:19:14.292
Keep straight. You're almost there.

384
00:19:14.375 --> 00:19:15.458
Yes. ma'am.

385
00:19:16.625 --> 00:19:19.708
Simmons. you call me ma'am one more time.
I'm gonna toss your ass out this car.

386
00:19:19.792 --> 00:19:20.833
You understand?

387
00:19:27.917 --> 00:19:29.833
[wind chimes tinkling]

388
00:20:00.458 --> 00:20:01.875
-Don't move. asshole!
-Okay.

389
00:20:01.958 --> 00:20:04.833
-You put the gun down. Do it now!
-Okay. yeah. okay. Easy.

390
00:20:04.917 --> 00:20:05.917
Slowly.

391
00:20:06.000 --> 00:20:08.375
Easy. easy. Okay?

392
00:20:08.458 --> 00:20:09.750
Turn around.

393
00:20:10.833 --> 00:20:12.083
Burroughs.

394
00:20:12.833 --> 00:20:14.208
What the hell are you doing here?

395
00:20:14.792 --> 00:20:18.000
The people who ordered you to kill me.

396
00:20:18.083 --> 00:20:20.125
-Do you know who they are?
-I have no idea.

397
00:20:20.208 --> 00:20:22.750
And I wish I had killed you because
if I had. I wouldn't be in this mess.

398
00:20:22.833 --> 00:20:24.000
You know where my son is?

399
00:20:24.083 --> 00:20:27.333
All I know is they've been watching you
since the day you arrived.

400
00:20:27.417 --> 00:20:29.875
And I was just supposed
to keep an eye on you. I was…

401
00:20:29.958 --> 00:20:32.333
I was supposed to babysit a child killer.

402
00:20:32.417 --> 00:20:35.958
And then your goddamn sister-in-law
shows up with that goddamn photograph.

403
00:20:36.042 --> 00:20:38.042
-And they want you dead.
-Is my son alive?

404
00:20:38.125 --> 00:20:40.917
I don't know. I am just doing
what they're telling me to do.

405
00:20:41.000 --> 00:20:42.292
How do you contact them?

406
00:20:49.333 --> 00:20:50.458
-Call them.
-I can't do that.

407
00:20:50.542 --> 00:20:52.917
-Yeah. you can.
-I can't. I need to protect my family!

408
00:20:53.000 --> 00:20:54.917
Look. you don't have to do this.
Please. listen.

409
00:20:55.000 --> 00:20:56.333
It's too late.

410
00:20:56.417 --> 00:20:59.042
-You can help me find my son.
-It's too late.

411
00:20:59.125 --> 00:21:01.917
I'm a loose end. and you have no idea
the reach these people have.

412
00:21:02.000 --> 00:21:04.250
-You never should've come here. Burroughs.
-What?

413
00:21:04.833 --> 00:21:06.458
-[gunshot]
-[bird wings flapping]

414
00:21:07.042 --> 00:21:08.792
[dog barking distantly]

415
00:21:09.542 --> 00:21:11.417
[crows cawing]

416
00:21:12.583 --> 00:21:14.583
[eerie music playing]

417
00:21:19.833 --> 00:21:21.667
[Rachel breathing heavily]

418
00:21:26.667 --> 00:21:28.125
David.

419
00:21:31.125 --> 00:21:32.333
He shot himself.

420
00:21:34.625 --> 00:21:36.083
Make a left. right here.

421
00:21:36.708 --> 00:21:38.125
7025.

422
00:21:44.500 --> 00:21:45.833
David. we have to go.

423
00:21:45.917 --> 00:21:48.250
Come on. Let's go. Come on.

424
00:21:48.333 --> 00:21:50.792
[tense music playing]

425
00:21:53.417 --> 00:21:55.083
[Greer] Ted Wesson!

426
00:22:11.125 --> 00:22:12.750
He's gone. Call it in.

427
00:22:13.458 --> 00:22:15.167
[car tires squealing]

428
00:22:18.333 --> 00:22:19.917
[tense music continuous]

429
00:22:24.667 --> 00:22:26.208
[yells]

430
00:22:26.292 --> 00:22:27.750
Damn it!

431
00:22:29.542 --> 00:22:31.625
-Why did he do that?
-They threatened his family.

432
00:22:31.708 --> 00:22:32.708
So he shot himself?

433
00:22:33.500 --> 00:22:34.708
To protect them.

434
00:22:34.792 --> 00:22:36.375
Did he tell you who has Matthew?

435
00:22:36.458 --> 00:22:38.250
[breathing heavily]

436
00:22:40.500 --> 00:22:41.500
No.

437
00:22:43.417 --> 00:22:44.792
They're covering their tracks.

438
00:22:46.417 --> 00:22:48.917
We gotta find Hilde Winslow
before they do.

439
00:22:51.208 --> 00:22:52.792
[cell doors buzzing]

440
00:23:04.583 --> 00:23:06.500
I want everything boxed and inventoried.

441
00:23:06.583 --> 00:23:07.583
Yes. sir.

442
00:23:09.583 --> 00:23:12.625
What time did Wesson take Burroughs
to the infirmary last night?

443
00:23:12.708 --> 00:23:14.000
Not sure.

444
00:23:15.500 --> 00:23:16.958
He forgot to sign him out.

445
00:23:17.042 --> 00:23:18.208
Forgot?

446
00:23:18.792 --> 00:23:19.750
It happens.

447
00:23:19.833 --> 00:23:21.000
Right.

448
00:23:32.792 --> 00:23:34.125
Psst. Hey.

449
00:23:34.208 --> 00:23:35.792
Did you happen to see Officer Wesson

450
00:23:35.875 --> 00:23:38.250
take David Burroughs
to the infirmary last night?

451
00:23:38.333 --> 00:23:39.750
I might have.

452
00:23:40.458 --> 00:23:42.042
I got trouble remembering things.

453
00:23:43.167 --> 00:23:45.667
Anything I can do to help jog your memory?

454
00:23:46.667 --> 00:23:50.208
Burroughs… has a flashlight.

455
00:23:51.792 --> 00:23:53.500
For reading after lights out.

456
00:23:54.208 --> 00:23:55.542
Can you get it for me?

457
00:23:55.625 --> 00:23:58.042
Come on. man. you know how this works.
Depends on what you saw.

458
00:24:01.250 --> 00:24:03.375
Wesson came for him
in the middle of the night.

459
00:24:03.458 --> 00:24:06.042
Which is strange. but not unheard of.

460
00:24:06.125 --> 00:24:08.292
But then he opens up his cell
with his emergency key.

461
00:24:10.208 --> 00:24:13.583
Instead of having the shift guard
buzz him in from the panel.

462
00:24:13.667 --> 00:24:17.000
Exactly. Now why would he do that
unless things wasn't on the up and up?

463
00:24:17.083 --> 00:24:19.000
-[cell phone vibrating]
-You know what I'm saying?

464
00:24:19.708 --> 00:24:21.417
Let me get you that flashlight.

465
00:24:21.500 --> 00:24:23.708
Hey. you on your way
back here with Wesson?

466
00:24:23.792 --> 00:24:24.625
No.

467
00:24:24.708 --> 00:24:27.292
-What do you mean no? Why not?
-Because he's dead.

468
00:24:27.375 --> 00:24:29.000
He-- What?

469
00:24:29.542 --> 00:24:30.375
How?

470
00:24:30.458 --> 00:24:32.333
Single gunshot wound to the head.

471
00:24:33.750 --> 00:24:34.792
[sighs]

472
00:24:34.875 --> 00:24:37.833
-Do we know who shot him?
-Have to wait for the ME and GSR.

473
00:24:37.917 --> 00:24:41.375
But a neighbor saw a man
matching David Burroughs's description

474
00:24:41.458 --> 00:24:43.500
enter the home minutes
before hearing a shot.

475
00:24:43.583 --> 00:24:45.417
You gotta be shitting me.

476
00:24:45.500 --> 00:24:47.458
And he wasn't alone.
Drove off with a woman.

477
00:24:47.542 --> 00:24:48.833
Rachel Mills.

478
00:24:50.292 --> 00:24:52.500
Any chance we can get them
before they hit the back roads?

479
00:24:52.583 --> 00:24:55.500
APB's out there. but our team
is spread across a 200-mile perimeter.

480
00:24:55.583 --> 00:24:57.583
No one thought he'd be
crazy enough to come back here.

481
00:24:57.667 --> 00:24:58.500
Yeah.

482
00:24:59.542 --> 00:25:01.750
Why would he risk coming back
just to kill Wesson?

483
00:25:01.833 --> 00:25:04.583
I'll dig into Wesson
and see what I can find.

484
00:25:04.667 --> 00:25:06.583
[ominous music playing]

485
00:25:08.958 --> 00:25:10.208
[David] How long to New York?

486
00:25:10.875 --> 00:25:12.000
[Rachel] Couple hours.

487
00:25:13.458 --> 00:25:14.583
You okay?

488
00:25:19.583 --> 00:25:20.583
You sure?

489
00:25:23.542 --> 00:25:25.208
Yeah. It's just intense.

490
00:25:27.042 --> 00:25:28.125
What Wesson did.

491
00:25:31.167 --> 00:25:32.792
Hit a little close to home.

492
00:25:34.750 --> 00:25:35.833
Yeah. how so?

493
00:25:36.792 --> 00:25:39.333
Mackenzie didn't tell you
how I was fired fromThe Globe.did he?

494
00:25:39.417 --> 00:25:40.417
No.

495
00:25:43.333 --> 00:25:47.667
I was investigating a series
of sexual assaults at Lemhall University.

496
00:25:49.292 --> 00:25:51.458
The faculty and a bunch
of powerful boosters

497
00:25:51.542 --> 00:25:53.708
were trying to sweep it all under the rug.

498
00:25:53.792 --> 00:25:57.875
One of the victims was this junior
named Catherine Tullo.

499
00:25:58.625 --> 00:26:00.417
who didn't want to come forward.

500
00:26:00.500 --> 00:26:04.375
You know? She didn't want to face
the scrutiny of victim-blaming.

501
00:26:07.458 --> 00:26:09.000
But I-I pushed her.

502
00:26:11.833 --> 00:26:13.083
I really pushed.

503
00:26:17.000 --> 00:26:19.833
Until she agreed to go on the record.

504
00:26:20.958 --> 00:26:22.083
Um…

505
00:26:24.333 --> 00:26:26.792
And the night before
we were supposed to meet.

506
00:26:28.042 --> 00:26:29.333
Catherine took her own life.

507
00:26:33.125 --> 00:26:34.542
I pushed her too hard.

508
00:26:34.625 --> 00:26:35.667
It was…

509
00:26:40.167 --> 00:26:41.875
All I could see was the story.

510
00:26:42.542 --> 00:26:44.042
You can't blame yourself.

511
00:26:44.833 --> 00:26:46.083
Her parents did.

512
00:26:48.125 --> 00:26:52.000
They suedThe Globe
for wrongful death. and I lost my job.

513
00:26:54.708 --> 00:26:56.208
They lost their daughter.

514
00:26:59.625 --> 00:27:02.792
You're a good person. Rachel.

515
00:27:07.250 --> 00:27:09.292
Even if you're
aiding and abetting a fugitive.

516
00:27:09.958 --> 00:27:11.208
[chuckling softly]

517
00:27:12.875 --> 00:27:14.542
[cell phone vibrating]

518
00:27:16.583 --> 00:27:17.875
[Rachel] Where'd that come from?

519
00:27:18.792 --> 00:27:19.833
It's Wesson's.

520
00:27:21.708 --> 00:27:23.333
[vibrating continues]

521
00:27:25.417 --> 00:27:26.708
[keypad beeps]

522
00:27:29.167 --> 00:27:30.917
[man on phone]Mr. Burroughs. I presume?

523
00:27:31.000 --> 00:27:34.125
-Who's this?
-I heard you paid Officer Wesson a visit.

524
00:27:36.042 --> 00:27:37.958
The police think you killed him.

525
00:27:38.625 --> 00:27:40.583
That should speed
your capture along nicely.

526
00:27:41.542 --> 00:27:44.167
-Where's Matthew?
-Oh. David.

527
00:27:44.750 --> 00:27:46.833
Your son died five years ago.

528
00:27:47.833 --> 00:27:49.333
You beat him to death. remember?

529
00:27:52.167 --> 00:27:53.667
I'm gonna find you.

530
00:27:55.542 --> 00:27:58.583
Even if you did. it wouldn't matter.

531
00:27:58.667 --> 00:28:01.250
The fact you think it would
shows how naive you are.

532
00:28:01.333 --> 00:28:04.708
How little you understand
what you are up against.

533
00:28:06.542 --> 00:28:08.292
I'm coming for my son.

534
00:28:10.542 --> 00:28:11.958
I'm coming for Matthew.

535
00:28:12.042 --> 00:28:13.625
[dramatic music playing]

536
00:28:16.875 --> 00:28:18.292
[sighing]

537
00:28:18.917 --> 00:28:21.125
[radio announcer]Looks like
there won't be any opportunity for rain.

538
00:28:21.208 --> 00:28:24.833
The next time you're probably gonna
need your rain gear will be Friday.

539
00:28:24.917 --> 00:28:26.917
And in the city. we might have rain…

540
00:28:27.000 --> 00:28:29.250
[Rachel] Still nothing on the local news
about your escape.

541
00:28:29.875 --> 00:28:31.625
So where's Hilde's PO box?

542
00:28:31.708 --> 00:28:32.750
Midtown.

543
00:28:34.250 --> 00:28:36.208
Doesn't open until 9:00 a.m.

544
00:28:37.042 --> 00:28:38.375
So we need a place to crash.

545
00:28:39.667 --> 00:28:40.958
I guess we sleep in the car.

546
00:28:42.875 --> 00:28:44.583
Maybe not. Do you remember Hayden?

547
00:28:45.167 --> 00:28:46.167
Yeah.

548
00:28:46.250 --> 00:28:47.583
What are you thinking?

549
00:28:48.917 --> 00:28:51.958
I'm thinking we need a burner phone.

550
00:28:52.042 --> 00:28:53.875
[turn signal clicking]

551
00:28:57.958 --> 00:28:58.792
You okay?

552
00:28:59.375 --> 00:29:01.750
Yeah. it's-- It's just a bit much.

553
00:29:02.333 --> 00:29:05.625
You know. I… kind of forgot
what real life looks like.

554
00:29:05.708 --> 00:29:08.708
To be fair. I just saw a woman's dog
wearing a Gucci sweater.

555
00:29:08.792 --> 00:29:10.875
so real life might be a stretch.

556
00:29:11.917 --> 00:29:13.083
Oh. there's a kiosk.

557
00:29:13.167 --> 00:29:14.875
[pedestrians chattering]

558
00:29:15.833 --> 00:29:17.708
[plaintive music playing]

559
00:29:40.917 --> 00:29:42.792
[car horns honking faintly]

560
00:29:44.083 --> 00:29:47.042
Hey. Can I get a prepaid phone. please?

561
00:29:48.750 --> 00:29:50.667
[funky music playing]

562
00:29:52.542 --> 00:29:56.500
[auctioneer] And finally.
we have Hendrick Sorgh'sA Kitchen.

563
00:29:56.583 --> 00:29:58.958
Shall we start the bidding at $500.000?

564
00:29:59.042 --> 00:30:02.000
$500.000. $550.000.

565
00:30:02.083 --> 00:30:03.333
[cell phone vibrates]

566
00:30:03.417 --> 00:30:04.833
$600.000.

567
00:30:05.708 --> 00:30:07.250
$650.000.

568
00:30:07.875 --> 00:30:09.167
$700.000.

569
00:30:10.208 --> 00:30:11.542
$800.000.

570
00:30:11.625 --> 00:30:13.000
1.5.

571
00:30:13.500 --> 00:30:15.958
[auctioneer] $1.5 million.

572
00:30:16.708 --> 00:30:17.792
Going once.

573
00:30:18.750 --> 00:30:19.875
Twice.

574
00:30:20.375 --> 00:30:22.292
-[gavel bangs]
-Sold.

575
00:30:22.375 --> 00:30:23.458
[indistinct chatter]

576
00:30:23.542 --> 00:30:25.042
[cell phone ringing]

577
00:30:25.667 --> 00:30:27.417
-Hayden.
-[Hayden. on phone]Rachel.

578
00:30:27.500 --> 00:30:29.000
It's good to hear from you.

579
00:30:29.083 --> 00:30:32.542
Hey. I should have called you
a long time ago. um…

580
00:30:33.375 --> 00:30:35.875
AfterThe Globe.
I know I sort of disappeared.

581
00:30:35.958 --> 00:30:38.792
No. no. no. No apologies necessary.

582
00:30:38.875 --> 00:30:43.000
Hey. listen. I'm in Boston right now.
How about. uh. we get a drink. catch up?

583
00:30:43.083 --> 00:30:45.792
You know. I wish I could.
I'm actually in New York.

584
00:30:45.875 --> 00:30:48.000
which is the reason I'm calling.

585
00:30:48.583 --> 00:30:51.042
-Why do I feel a favor coming on?
-[Rachel laughs]

586
00:30:51.125 --> 00:30:52.375
Yeah. it's a crazy story.

587
00:30:52.458 --> 00:30:55.667
I had my purse stolen.
and without my ID and my credit card.

588
00:30:55.750 --> 00:30:57.000
I can't check into my hotel.

589
00:30:57.083 --> 00:30:59.500
So. I know this is a big ask.
but is there any way

590
00:30:59.583 --> 00:31:01.500
I could stay at your place
just for the night?

591
00:31:01.583 --> 00:31:02.708
Yeah. of course.

592
00:31:03.500 --> 00:31:06.167
Hey. look. I'll come down tomorrow
and we'll grab a bite.

593
00:31:06.250 --> 00:31:10.500
You know. I'd love that. but I'm just
here literally just for the night.

594
00:31:10.583 --> 00:31:12.292
Um. but maybe another time?

595
00:31:12.375 --> 00:31:13.708
I'm gonna hold you to it.

596
00:31:13.792 --> 00:31:15.000
[laughing]

597
00:31:15.083 --> 00:31:16.083
Um…

598
00:31:16.667 --> 00:31:18.792
I'll have the spare keys left
at the front desk for you.

599
00:31:18.875 --> 00:31:20.292
[sighing]

600
00:31:20.375 --> 00:31:22.875
-Thank you. Hayden.
-Yeah. anytime.

601
00:31:22.958 --> 00:31:24.458
And hey. Rachel. it's…

602
00:31:25.375 --> 00:31:27.917
-It's really good to hear from you.
-Yeah. you too.

603
00:31:29.333 --> 00:31:30.167
Bye.

604
00:31:30.708 --> 00:31:32.292
Hey. we're all set.

605
00:31:35.042 --> 00:31:37.208
[oldies playing on jukebox]

606
00:31:38.500 --> 00:31:39.417
Yeah.

607
00:31:40.167 --> 00:31:41.708
All right. thanks. Chopra.

608
00:31:42.625 --> 00:31:43.542
No sign of him.

609
00:31:45.333 --> 00:31:46.333
Thanks.

610
00:31:47.458 --> 00:31:52.083
So. I was doing some digging into Wesson.
and I found something odd.

611
00:31:52.167 --> 00:31:53.625
He's been getting $1.000 a month

612
00:31:53.708 --> 00:31:57.167
for the last five years
from this company called REH Holdings.

613
00:31:57.250 --> 00:31:58.833
[Williams] Sounds like a shell company.

614
00:31:58.917 --> 00:32:01.083
Mm-hmm. It's registered in the Caymans.

615
00:32:01.708 --> 00:32:03.292
It's untraceable even for us.

616
00:32:03.375 --> 00:32:04.292
Hmm.

617
00:32:04.375 --> 00:32:07.250
The payments started the month
that Burroughs arrived at Briggs.

618
00:32:08.292 --> 00:32:10.208
You think someone's paying
to keep tabs on him?

619
00:32:11.083 --> 00:32:13.042
I'm saying the timing lines up.

620
00:32:14.708 --> 00:32:16.708
You know. you might be right about that.

621
00:32:16.792 --> 00:32:17.917
Don't hear that often.

622
00:32:18.000 --> 00:32:20.417
I talked to the inmate
next to Burroughs's cell.

623
00:32:20.500 --> 00:32:21.792
[Greer] Mm-hmm.

624
00:32:21.875 --> 00:32:26.500
He told me Wesson came and got him out
of his cell in the middle of the night.

625
00:32:27.208 --> 00:32:30.125
But he used his emergency key
to open the cell door

626
00:32:30.208 --> 00:32:31.958
instead of getting it buzzed open.

627
00:32:33.167 --> 00:32:34.583
He wanted it off the books.

628
00:32:37.542 --> 00:32:41.708
What if Wesson tried to kill Burroughs
last night and not the other way around?

629
00:32:42.417 --> 00:32:46.958
Maybe Burroughs decides to hang around
and settle the score.

630
00:32:47.042 --> 00:32:49.208
Yeah. definitely possible.

631
00:32:51.083 --> 00:32:53.583
But it doesn't say anything
about where he's going next.

632
00:32:53.667 --> 00:32:57.333
I don't suppose this inmate of yours
told you where he was headed?

633
00:32:57.417 --> 00:32:58.542
No.

634
00:32:59.958 --> 00:33:04.292
Goddamn it. I promised the guy
I'd get him Burroughs's flashlight.

635
00:33:04.375 --> 00:33:05.208
Well…

636
00:33:09.083 --> 00:33:10.542
[Greer typing]

637
00:33:10.625 --> 00:33:11.583
What?

638
00:33:11.667 --> 00:33:16.083
Briggs sent over the inventory list
from Burroughs's cell a couple hours ago.

639
00:33:19.542 --> 00:33:22.042
There's no flashlight on this list.

640
00:33:23.208 --> 00:33:25.167
[officer] We toss the cell every week.

641
00:33:25.750 --> 00:33:28.542
If he's hiding something.
it's a surprise to me.

642
00:33:29.500 --> 00:33:31.625
[sighing] Let's start with the mattress.

643
00:33:46.208 --> 00:33:48.333
[foreboding music playing]

644
00:33:59.875 --> 00:34:01.083
Here we go.

645
00:34:04.708 --> 00:34:05.583
Huh.

646
00:34:09.333 --> 00:34:10.583
[Greer] What is it?

647
00:34:11.375 --> 00:34:13.292
It's his son's case file.

648
00:34:15.125 --> 00:34:17.500
Hey. He circled this name.

649
00:34:17.583 --> 00:34:19.042
Hilde Winslow.

650
00:34:19.125 --> 00:34:21.417
That's the witness
who saw him bury the bat.

651
00:34:21.500 --> 00:34:23.250
Her testimony helped put him away.

652
00:34:23.333 --> 00:34:25.750
If he killed Wesson to settle the score.
she might be next.

653
00:34:30.292 --> 00:34:31.667
[door lock tumbles]

654
00:34:50.042 --> 00:34:52.250
-[exhales]
-Yeah. it's a lot. right?

655
00:34:59.542 --> 00:35:00.958
Empty fridge.

656
00:35:03.250 --> 00:35:04.917
As usual. nothing.

657
00:35:08.167 --> 00:35:11.833
I'm gonna pop out to the bodega and see
if I can scrounge something up for dinner.

658
00:35:16.375 --> 00:35:17.208
You good?

659
00:35:20.333 --> 00:35:21.583
Matthew's out there.

660
00:35:23.750 --> 00:35:24.875
Somewhere.

661
00:35:24.958 --> 00:35:26.792
[somber music playing]

662
00:35:29.792 --> 00:35:31.292
Be right back.

663
00:35:31.375 --> 00:35:33.250
[footsteps receding]

664
00:35:33.958 --> 00:35:35.375
[door opening]

665
00:35:36.375 --> 00:35:37.792
[David sighs softly]

666
00:35:37.875 --> 00:35:38.833
[door closes]

667
00:35:39.333 --> 00:35:41.583
-[music playing faintly]
-[patrons chattering]

668
00:35:45.417 --> 00:35:47.208
Nothing on David getting caught.

669
00:35:47.292 --> 00:35:49.500
Should've never
gotten you involved in any of this.

670
00:35:49.583 --> 00:35:51.167
A little late for that. old man.

671
00:35:51.250 --> 00:35:52.500
I'm serious. Adam.
They could take your shield.

672
00:35:52.583 --> 00:35:53.875
At the very least.
they're gonna suspend you.

673
00:35:53.958 --> 00:35:54.958
I know.

674
00:35:55.042 --> 00:35:56.000
Adam.

675
00:35:57.042 --> 00:35:59.250
It's David. He's family.

676
00:36:01.375 --> 00:36:03.250
Did he tell you
who he thought was behind this?

677
00:36:03.333 --> 00:36:04.208
No.

678
00:36:06.333 --> 00:36:08.042
[cell phone vibrating]

679
00:36:13.542 --> 00:36:15.500
[dramatic music playing]

680
00:36:16.583 --> 00:36:17.583
[puts phone down]

681
00:36:22.167 --> 00:36:23.625
You gonna be okay in my guest room?

682
00:36:23.708 --> 00:36:25.500
Where are you going?

683
00:36:25.583 --> 00:36:27.417
Uh. I got something to take care of.

684
00:36:27.500 --> 00:36:28.667
At this hour?

685
00:36:30.958 --> 00:36:32.125
I'll see you later. Pops.

686
00:36:36.250 --> 00:36:37.667
[door opening]

687
00:36:39.750 --> 00:36:41.000
[door closing]

688
00:36:41.083 --> 00:36:43.000
[faint chatter over TV]

689
00:36:44.875 --> 00:36:46.500
Hey. I'm back.

690
00:36:59.500 --> 00:37:01.000
[typing]

691
00:37:12.667 --> 00:37:14.000
[door closing]

692
00:37:19.375 --> 00:37:20.583
I borrowed some clothes.

693
00:37:21.167 --> 00:37:23.000
-I hope that's okay.
-Of course.

694
00:37:23.083 --> 00:37:24.708
[plastic crinkling]

695
00:37:28.542 --> 00:37:29.958
[TV newscaster 1]
And we have breaking news.

696
00:37:30.042 --> 00:37:32.042
Convicted child killer David Burroughs

697
00:37:32.125 --> 00:37:35.208
escaped Briggs Penitentiary
earlier this morning.

698
00:37:35.292 --> 00:37:37.625
Police are still
on the hunt for Burroughs.

699
00:37:37.708 --> 00:37:39.917
whose whereabouts remain unknown.

700
00:37:40.000 --> 00:37:42.167
In a news conference this evening…

701
00:37:42.250 --> 00:37:43.375
Don't look at that.

702
00:37:43.458 --> 00:37:45.333
…their search has widened…

703
00:37:45.917 --> 00:37:48.083
Bodega dinner. All right.

704
00:37:50.250 --> 00:37:51.917
-Looks great.
-[laughs softly]

705
00:37:52.625 --> 00:37:54.417
You know what? Hayden's gotta have
a bottle of something

706
00:37:54.500 --> 00:37:56.167
that's gonna make this
taste very expensive.

707
00:37:56.875 --> 00:37:59.417
[TV newscaster 1]Officials have
warned that anyone found

708
00:37:59.500 --> 00:38:02.333
to be aiding or abetting Burroughs
in his escape

709
00:38:02.417 --> 00:38:04.375
will be arrested and prosecuted to the…

710
00:38:05.458 --> 00:38:07.625
Chopin martini. Dry. three olives. please.

711
00:38:07.708 --> 00:38:09.292
-Thanks.
-[bartender] Coming up.

712
00:38:10.208 --> 00:38:13.625
[TV newscaster 2]…murderer escaped
from Briggs Penitentiary earlier today

713
00:38:13.708 --> 00:38:15.542
and is still considered a danger…

714
00:38:15.625 --> 00:38:18.458
The FBI has not yet
made an official statement.

715
00:38:18.542 --> 00:38:20.167
but the search remains ongoing.

716
00:38:20.250 --> 00:38:22.083
Those with information on Burroughs

717
00:38:22.167 --> 00:38:25.583
are encouraged to contact
their local police department.

718
00:38:25.667 --> 00:38:29.292
Authorities are calling this
an all-hands-on-deck situation…

719
00:38:30.333 --> 00:38:32.333
[menacing music playing]

720
00:38:45.042 --> 00:38:45.917
[Rachel]Hey.

721
00:38:47.250 --> 00:38:48.333
We're gonna find him.

722
00:38:49.833 --> 00:38:50.917
Together.

723
00:38:54.375 --> 00:38:57.167
["Change (In the House of Flies)"
by Deftones playing]

724
00:39:14.708 --> 00:39:16.375
♪ I watched you… ♪

725
00:39:16.458 --> 00:39:19.458
Philip. what the hell's going on?

726
00:39:20.167 --> 00:39:21.583
Call me back.

727
00:39:22.417 --> 00:39:27.000
♪ Into a fly ♪

728
00:39:29.208 --> 00:39:32.458
♪ I looked away ♪

729
00:39:34.042 --> 00:39:38.000
♪ You were on fire ♪

730
00:39:52.208 --> 00:39:53.125
Yeah.

731
00:39:54.875 --> 00:39:56.125
I'm almost done here.

732
00:39:58.208 --> 00:40:00.042
Yes. I understand.

733
00:40:02.167 --> 00:40:04.000
It's being taken care of.

734
00:40:10.375 --> 00:40:14.167
♪ I took you home ♪

735
00:40:16.625 --> 00:40:19.917
♪ Then I laughed ♪

736
00:40:21.458 --> 00:40:25.708
♪ I watched a change ♪

737
00:40:25.792 --> 00:40:28.167
♪ In you ♪

738
00:40:29.042 --> 00:40:32.500
♪ It's like you never♪

739
00:40:32.583 --> 00:40:35.417
♪ Had wings ♪

740
00:40:35.500 --> 00:40:38.458
♪ Ah. ah. ah ♪

741
00:40:38.542 --> 00:40:42.333
♪ Ah. ah. ah ♪

742
00:40:42.417 --> 00:40:44.333
♪ Ah. ah ♪

743
00:40:45.417 --> 00:40:47.333
[song ends]

744
00:40:47.417 --> 00:40:49.333
